<bioghist id="a2" encodinganalog="5451_"><head>Historical Note</head><p>Charles T. Sacket (d. 1936) was a Livingston, Montana engineer. He served in the U.S. Army in World War I and settled in Montana shortly after his discharge in 1919. Married to Berenice Geer Sacket in Chicago, 1917, the couple had one son, Charles Jr. (1918-1943).</p></bioghist>
<scopecontent id="a3" encodinganalog="5202_"><p>The Cooke City mining district maps in this collection were all allegedly drawn by Sacket, although three predate his residence in Livingston. The maps show geographic features as well as mining claim boundaries.</p></scopecontent>
<accessrestrict id="a14" encodinganalog="506"><p>This collection is open for research.</p></accessrestrict>
<acqinfo id="a19" encodinganalog="541"><p>The Charles T. Sacket maps of the Cooke City Mining District were donated to Special Collections by Richard C. Waite, Bozeman, Montana, on September 27, 1989.</p></acqinfo>
